31/01/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A delegation of NATO experts in the field of classified information finalised a six-day visit to Romania Thursday (30 January). The experts reviewed the legislative framework and the work of the Romanian National Register Office of Secret State Information. Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase said after a meeting with the visitors that the overall assessment was positive and, despite some recommendations for improvement, the country could go on with its NATO membership process. (Rompres - 31/01/03)
